Hong Kong Stocks Fall 0.66 Percent
The turnover was 8.426 billion HK dollars (1.08 billion U.S. dollars),
an increase of 1.225 billion HK dollars (157 million U.S. dollars) from
7.201 billion HK dollars (923 million U.S. dollars) Tuesday.
Of the four sub-indices, only Utilities rose 0.82 percent, but Finance,
Properties and Commerce & Industry all dropped 0.12 percent, 0.48
percent and 1.27 percent, respectively.
China-related stocks ended lower with the Hang Seng China Enterprises
Index down 0.10 percent and Hang Seng China-Affiliated Corporations
Index down 4.41 percent.
The Hang Seng IT Index and Hang Seng IT Portfolio Index declined 1.32
percent and 2.09 percent.
The blue chips went up 46.23 points, or 0.30 percent, to open at
15,409.38 Wednesday, but the stock prices went down to close the
morning session at 15,258.12.
